subject: p13475033
Findings: The heart is at the upper limits of normal size. The mediastinal and hilar contours appear unchanged. There is mild interstitial abnormality suggestive of slight fluid overload, but no focal consolidation. The lungs are hyperinflated. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. A moderate anterior wedge compression deformity situated along the lower thoracic spine appears unchanged since the prior studies.
Impression: Similar mild interstitial abnormality which could be seen with slight fluid overload.
